{"lemma":"مُتَرادِفٌ","slug":"مُتَرادِفٌ","root":"ر.د.ف","root_slug":"ر-د-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-د-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n15276"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%AA%D9%8E%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%81%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"synonymous with each other"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of the verb تَرَادَفَ (tarādafa, “to become synonymous”)."},"ipa":["/mu.ta.raː.dif/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n15276","headword_ar":"مُتَرَادِفٌ","root":"rdf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", as a conventional term in lexicology,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Synonymous:"},{"kind":"text","text":"you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alofaAZN mutaraAdifapN","text_ar":"اَلْفَاظٌ مُتَرَادِفَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"synonymous words"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expressions."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mz, 27th"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwE","text_ar":"نوع"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [Loosely explained in the K by the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano yakuwna A@somFA","text_ar":"اَنْ يَكُونَ ا@سْمًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"li$~Yo'K waAHidK","text_ar":"لِشّىْءٍ وَاحِدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"significant of one thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$otarakN","text_ar":"مُشْتَرَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. “ homonymous: ” and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmutaraAdifapu","text_ar":"المُتَرَادِفَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is expl. in the O,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"An tkwn A^asomaA='F l$Y'K wAHdK","text_ar":"ان تكون اَسْمَا=ءً لشىءٍ واحدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and is said to be post-classical.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaraAdifaAtN","text_ar":"مُتَرَادِفَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[its pl. when used"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1069},{"kind":"text","text":"as a subst.] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Synonyms;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"single,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"simple, words denoting the same thing considered in one and the same respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaraAdifaAni","text_ar":"مُتَرَادِفَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"differ from the noun and the definition [thereof], because these [generally] are not both single words; and from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutabaAyinaAni","text_ar":"مُتَبَايِنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or “ two disparates ”] such as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ayofu","text_ar":"السَّيْفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~aArimu","text_ar":"الصَّارِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because these denote the same thing considered in two different respects, the one in respect of the substance, and the other in respect of the quality: (Fakhred-Deen [Er-Rázee] in the Mz, 27th"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwE","text_ar":"نوع"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or they may be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two simple words, as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~ayovu","text_ar":"اللَّيْثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^asadu","text_ar":"الاَسَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two compound expressions, as,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juluwsu All~ayovi","text_ar":"جُلُوسُ اللَّيْثِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quEuwdu AlA^asadi","text_ar":"قُعُودُ الاَسَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single word and a compound expression,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almuz~u","text_ar":"المُزُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHulowu AlHaAmiDu","text_ar":"الحُلْوُ الحَامِضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Kull p. 130.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muraAdifu lafoZK","text_ar":"مُرَادِفُ لَفْظٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] [This art. is wanting in the copies of the L and TA to which I have had access.]"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}